Time to time it's useful to force a page break. There is a [trick to avoid weird issue](https://www.sitepoint.com/community/t/bottom-margin-issue-with-chrome-vs-ie/286465/3). You always need to specify at least an unbreakable space in the page break:

```html
&nbsp;
```

```sass
.page-break {
    display: none;
}

@media print {
    .page-break {
        page-break-before: always;
        display: block;
    }
}`
```

To avoid to your content shrink to the left:

```sass
table#page-layout {
  width: 100%;
}
```

```sass
.page-header, .page-header-space,
.page-footer, .page-footer-space {
  display: none;
}

@media print {
    .page-header, .page-header-space,
    .page-footer, .page-footer-space {
      display: block;
      height: $page-margin-header;
      width: 100%;
    }
}
```

You must specify the page's size and the page's orientation. Otherwize `@Page` margin information won't be taken into account:

```sass
@media print {
    @page {
        size: A4 portrait;
        margin: 0;
    }
}
```

```sass
table#page-layout {
  & > tbody > tr > td {
      padding-left: $page-margin-side;
      padding-right: $page-margin-side;
  }
}
```

[How it looks](/blog/test/page-margin-print-css).

Here is the code of that example:


```html

    
        &nbsp;
    
    
        
            {%- block page_content %}{% endblock page_content -%}
        
    
    
        &nbsp;
    





    {%- block print_footer -%}
        Footer
    {%- endblock print_footer -%}

```

```sass
//$page-height: 297mm;
//$page-width: 210mm;
$page-margin-header: 10mm;
$page-margin-side: 10mm;
$page-margin-footer: 20mm;

.page-header, .page-header-space,
.page-footer, .page-footer-space {
  display: none;
}

table#page-layout {
  width: 100%;
}

.page-break {
  display: none;
}

@media print {
  @page
  {
    size: A4 portrait;
    margin: 0;
  }

  body {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .page-break {
    page-break-before: always;
    display: block;
  }

  .page-content {
    background-color: #fff;
  }

  table#page-layout {
    & > tbody > tr > td {
      padding-left: $page-margin-side;
      padding-right: $page-margin-side;
    }
  }

  .page-header, .page-header-space,
  .page-footer, .page-footer-space {
    display: block;
    height: $page-margin-header;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .page-footer, .page-footer-space {
    height: $page-margin-footer;
  }

  .page-header {
    padding-top: 2mm;
    text-align: center;
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
  }
  .page-footer {
    padding-top: 2mm;
    text-align: center;
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 0;
  }

}
```
